The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Cognizant profit jumps 34%
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Cognizant profit jumps 34%
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, May 4: Nasdaq-listed Cognizant Technology Solutions has posted a 34 per cent rise in net profit at $151.5 million, or 49 cents a share, for the quarter ended March 31 against $113.1 million, or 38 cents a share, in the year-ago period.         
	This is for the fifth straight quarter that the firm has beaten estimates to post profit.         
	Revenue rose 29 per cent to $959.7 million from $745.9 million a year ago. Buoyed by the performance, the company expects revenues for the second quarter of 2010 to be at least $1.015 billion. It has raised its 2010 revenue growth guidance to 25 per cent from 20 per cent.         
	Against the backdrop of an improving macroeconomic environment, our first quarter results confirm that our strategy of reinvestment continues to provide the platform for growth, CEO Francisco DSouza said.        
	Our investments during the downturn  in new areas, including consulting and emerging markets, new solutions such as enterprise analytics, and technologies such as cloud and mobile computing  have left us stronger than ever before, he said.        
	The companys net headcount addition exceeded 7,100 employees during the quarter, taking its global headcount to over 85,500.                                                                                                                                       
